<span id="freeTextContainer6157705514855788733">From the resources to the first-hand accounts to the stellar advice, Kelly Huegel&apos;s &quot;GLBTQ: The Survival Guide for Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual, Transgender, and Questioning Teens,&quot; (which is the second edition) is beyond important, relevant, and helpful. I only wish that I had read the book sooner. </span>
  <span id="freeText6157705514855788733" style="display:none">From the resources to the first-hand accounts to the stellar advice, Kelly Huegel's "GLBTQ: The Survival Guide for Gay, Lesbian, Bisexual, Transgender, and Questioning Teens," (which is the second edition) is beyond important, relevant, and helpful. I only wish that I had read the book sooner. </span>
