<div id="review_2685493492" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2685493492" />
    <a title="Brianna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/91880167-brianna"><img alt="Brianna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1594097819p2/91880167.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2685493492?book_show_action=true">Jan 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brianna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brianna" href="/user/show/91880167-brianna">Brianna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781631983023" href="/book/show/39741570-lgbtq">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/91880167-brianna?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/91880167-brianna?shelf=lgbt">lgbt</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/91880167-brianna?shelf=arcs">arcs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2685493492" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1302594798072146565">ARC provided by the publisher via Edelweiss in exchange for an honest review.<br/><br/><i> What label is big enough to encompass the expansiveness and capacity of the human heart? </i><br/><br/>I definitely thought this book was a good read! As a member of the LGBTQ community, who studies sexuality studies in school and is pretty confident in my sexuality, I have to say that a lot of what I read in the book wasn&apos;t of news to me. But, I definitely think that this book is relevant and can definitely help people who are firs</span>
  <span id="freeText1302594798072146565" style="display:none">ARC provided by the publisher via Edelweiss in exchange for an honest review.<br /><br /><i> What label is big enough to encompass the expansiveness and capacity of the human heart? </i><br /><br />I definitely thought this book was a good read! As a member of the LGBTQ community, who studies sexuality studies in school and is pretty confident in my sexuality, I have to say that a lot of what I read in the book wasn't of news to me. But, I definitely think that this book is relevant and can definitely help people who are first coming to terms with their sexuality and need a bit of guidance. <br /><br />I think the best part about this book was the endless list of resources that were provided. Each chapter is filled with dozens of books, websites, and social media accounts of places where LGBTQ+ teens could go to learn more. Even I found a lot of resources that I didn't know existed. Another thing I love about the book were the varieties of "checklists" sprinkled throughout. For example, there was one checklist that LGBTQ+ teens should use to ask themselves if they are ready to date. There are a lot of other checklists about mental health, abusive relationships (an Abusive Relationship Self-Test), as well as a variety of other things that teens should use to assess their situation. I really loved these. I also loved how step-by-step the book was. For example, in the "Coming Out" section, there was a step-by-step process on how to come out to family members that was really helpful. There was also a detailed description on what to do when realizing that you're transgender. The fact that situations like these are broken down step-by-step will definitely help questioning readers feel less overwhelmed and more confident in what they may need to do next. <br /><br />I also love how this book deals with the topics of sex, intersectionality, the gender binary, and more modern ways of thinking about sexuality and gender. The author doesn't assume that the reader is completely clueless about gender and sexuality, and doesn't shy away from the unfortunate circumstances that LGBTQ+ face. But, it gives questioning and potentially scared LGBTQ+ teens options, support, and hope. <br /><br />I definitely wish this book was available everywhere--from the children's section at libraries to in high-school classrooms to community centre classrooms. The 2018 edition of this book is one I think every LGBTQ+ teen coming to terms with their sexuality needs to read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1302594798072146565" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


